---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Colophon — Kavya" description="How this site is built.">
  <article class="container measure page">
    <span class="eyebrow">Colophon</span>
    <h1>How this site is built</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A short note for the curious — and a small reminder to myself that the medium is part of the message.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Built with</strong> Astro, hand-written CSS, no template.</li>
        <li><strong>Type</strong> set in Fraunces (display) and Inter (body).</li>
        <li><strong>Hosted</strong> on Vercel; deployed automatically from GitHub.</li>
        <li><strong>Measured</strong> with Google Analytics 4 and Search Console.</li>
        <li><strong>Newsletter</strong> runs on Kit.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Everything here — the design, the writing, the growth — is something I’m doing on purpose and documenting in the <a href="/lab">Growth Lab</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .page { padding-block: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem); }
  .page h1 { margin: 0.5rem 0 1.2rem; }
</style>
